---
import { Footer } from "../components/Footer";
import "../styles/tailwind.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="generator" content="Astro" />
    <title>Theory - Ryan Johnson</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-background text-foreground selection:bg-stone-200 dark:selection:bg-stone-800 min-h-screen flex flex-col noise-bg">
    <main class="container mx-auto px-6 py-12 max-w-4xl flex-1 structural-border mt-8 border-t-0 p-8 md:p-12 mb-12">
      <nav class="mb-12 flex items-center justify-between border-b border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 pb-4">
        <a href="/" class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-stone-500 hover:text-stone-900 dark:hover:text-stone-100 transition-colors">/ Home</a>
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-300 dark:text-stone-700">Internal Linkage</span>
      </nav>
      
      <div class="space-y-12">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h1 class="text-5xl font-heading tracking-tighter">Theory of Development</h1>
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-stone-500">Ref. ABOUT_CORE</p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose-stone dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed font-sans">
            This digital space is a manifestation of structural honesty and minimalist architectural principles.
          </p>
          <div class="h-px w-24 bg-stone-300 dark:bg-stone-700 my-8"></div>
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 font-sans">
            Current stack involves Astro for static generation, SolidJS for interactive logic, and a bespoke Tailwind-driven design system optimized for clarity and performance.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>

    <Footer client:load />
  </body>
</html>